The Terrace at Sandton Gate is a new development perfectly positioned on the doorstep of the Sandton CBD. Sandton Gate is one of the most sought-after mixed-use precincts in South Africa as it balances the suburban lifestyle with all the benefits of world-class urban living through its blend of commercial, residential, and natural green spaces. Reserve your apartment at The Terrace in Sandton Gate. The popularity of mixed-use precincts in South Africa is rising due to the advantages they offer – such as safety, security, and convenience – and The Terrace at Sandton Gate is no exception. The Terrace residents will benefit from having an extensive range of Sandton Gate amenities and facilities within a comfortable walking distance, including: Shops
Restaurants
Coffee cafes
Planet Fitness gym
Beauticians
Salons
Premium office space This provides a seamless lifestyle and smarter city living, while secure access to Johannesburg’s longest stream and green belt – the Braamfontein Spruit greenbelt – ensures you don’t lose touch with nature. You also benefit from the community offered by a mixed-use precinct, which is designed to enable interaction and allow people to get to know each other. Additionally, the safety offered by the precinct – as well as The Terrace’s 24-hour security, electric fencing, and CCTV surveillance – mean you can enjoy long walks in the Braamfontein Spruit without worrying about safety. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-586798" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture2.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture2.jpg 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture2-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The Terrace’s apartments are equipped with luxury interiors and premium finishes, and each boasts its own private balcony as well as access to a communal swimming pool, sun deck, and relaxation area. You can choose from a variety of two-bedroom apartments with several layout options, as well as three-bedroom penthouses. The two-bedroom apartments comprise the following: Two basement parking bays
Private balcony with shade
View of, and secure access to, the Braamfontein Spruit
Miele electric stove, oven, and extractor
Pre-paid electricity meter
Fibre connection ready The three-bedroom penthouses offer an additional parking bay, a private rooftop garden, and bespoke finishes. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-586804" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture3.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture3.jpg 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture3-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Construction on The Terrace apartments began in 2021, and you can now reserve yours with a R5,000 deposit. The Terrace apartments start at R1,849,000 for a two-bedroom, one-bathroom luxury unit – and you can arrange a viewing with Craft Homes. These luxury apartments also make great investment opportunities for four major reasons: luxury apartments are in-demand, they command higher rental prices, their high-quality finishes require less maintenance, and they are more affordable than houses. Click here to reserve your apartment at The Terrace in Sandton Gate. You can see photos of apartments at The Terrace below. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-586808" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture4.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture4.jpg 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture4-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-586810" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture5.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture5.jpg 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Picture5-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width